[quote=“I need a username, post:3, topic:402199”]if you get an error “javac is not a recognized blabla…” with that code ^.^
do this:
Ok… first open up command prompt and run the following command:
dir C:\progra~1\java
Write down the file that looks like jdk#.#_##
something like that ^.^
use:
“C:\progra~1\java\THAT FIle you wrote down\bin\javac.exe”

instead of javac[/quote]

Or he can set the classpath so he doesn’t need to worry about it.
